headline: Alphabet, Chip Stocks Lead Tech-Fueled Market Rebound
summary: Chip stocks and other big technology shares rallied Monday, extending Friday’s gains and suggesting that fears of an AI bubble are receding.  Semiconductor companies  Broadcom Advanced Micro Devices  and  Micron Technology  were among the big winners, while  Tesla  and Google parent  Alphabet  both added more than 6%.  A fund tracking the “Magnificent Seven” tech stocks added 3.3%, its largest increase since May.
